<p>This article provides insight into connectivity issues in Middle East. Ottoman empire built a grand railway network in 1900 (known as Hejaz Railways). It had vitat political, economic and social influencd on entire region.&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Britishers destroyed the railway network in 1916 (during WW I)&nbsp; to disintegrate Arab region. No attempts were made to revive this rail network after 1916.</p>
